# 1. クリスマスの予定は

Rui: (Another day of high-intensity lessons.)
Rui: (I'm so grateful that I get to learn so much about theatre from the fundamentals.)
Rui: (Whether that's techniques unique to acting while singing or playing female characters...)
Rui: (Doing things that I normally don't get to will not only help me communicate better with actors, but also broaden my perspective as a director.)
Rui: (I have to think Emu is also learning quite a lot about the operational side of—)
???: Oh! Ruiiiiii!
Rui: Huh?
Emu: I had a feeling it was you! Did you have a wonderhoy day?!
Rui: Hello, Emu. Are you also on your way home?
Emu: Yup! I learned a lot again today☆
Emu: Huh? Where's Tsukasa? Is he not with you?
Rui: He said he's going to practice on his own for a bit in order to master what we covered in class today as quickly as possible.
Emu: Really...?! Nene's doing the same thing! She just sent me a message saying that she's also gonna practice on her own!
Emu: That means I need to keep learning as much as I can too!
Rui: Hehe. And I'm sure you will.
Rui: By the way, Emu, what have you been learning about recently?
Emu: Oh, so they showed me around the theatre and...
Emu: Really?! You guys got to practice that today?!
Rui: Yes. Ballet's intriguing since the elegant movements can surely be applied to quite a number of situations.
Rui: Tsukasa even said that he'd like to try using some during our next show.
Emu: Our next show...? Oh, the one we're gonna do at the ski resort?! I really love the story you came up with for that, Rui☆
Emu: I can't wait since it's been so long since the last time we did a show together♪
Rui: Hehe. Yes, it has.
Rui: We'll need to thank your brothers once again for giving us this wonderful opportunity.
Rui: A show on the slope of a ski resort...?
Keisuke: Yes, it's a subsidiary of the Otori Group, and they're apparently going to put on a Christmas show for children.
Keisuke: A few cast members from Phoenix Wonderland are scheduled to perform...
Keisuke: But the resort specifically asked for you to direct the show.
Rui: I'm honored, but... Why me?
Shosuke: Apparently, the owner of the resort has seen your troupe perform.
Shosuke: And he particularly enjoyed the stage effects.
Rui: I see. That explains the situation.
Keisuke: Of course, you don't have to accept since we know you're all busy right now with your Morinomiya lessons.
Rui: I appreciate the concern... But I'd like to accept this offer.
Rui: I haven't been getting many chances to direct lately. And more importantly, it's not every day that you get to put on a show at a ski resort.
Rui: I'm looking forward to this opportunity since I gained many new perspectives in terms of directing the last time I did this.
Keisuke: I see... Then, I'll let them know that you're accepting their offer.
Rui: Thank you very much. Oh, while we're on the subject...
Rui: Would it be possible for me and the others to accept this offer as Wonderlands×Showtime?
Shosuke: As Wonderlands×Showtime?
Rui: Yes, since the others also stand to benefit from the experience of performing at such a unique place.
Shosuke: Right...
Keisuke: Understood. Then, I'll see what they say about it.
Keisuke: They'll likely need some time to respond, so we'll let you know when we hear back from them.
Rui: Of course. Thank you very much.
Rui: I promise to make the most of this wonderful opportunity I've been given.
Rui: Now that Tsukasa and Nene have also agreed to be in it, I'm looking forward to this show even more...
Rui: Not to mention that it's been quite a while since I last directed a show, so there's a long list of things I've been wanting to try... Hehe. Think about all the possibilities.
Emu: Hehe. You sound all fired up, Rui!
Emu: By the way, have you already figured out a plan for this show?
Rui: I'm still coming up with ideas... We'll be doing it on the evening of Christmas Day, so my goal is to make it feel like a dreamlike experience.
Rui: In particular, I'd like to make the climax an unforgettable moment...
Rui: I'm currently thinking about using lanterns to create a mystical atmosphere.
Emu: Lanterns...! I bet it's gonna look sparkly, glowy and really pretty...
Emu: Let me know if you need me to help you with anything! I promise to work super duper hard on stage and behind the scenes when the day comes☆
Rui: Thank you. I appreciate the offer.
Rui: Let's all do our best to make our show a wonderful Christmas present for our audience.
Emu: Yeah!
